note.p: There may be a mistake here. It would make more sense for the effect of the myrbolani to hinder the effect of the violet than itself, given the point being illustrated.
The word cumachta is written in the margin to the right but it is not clear where it is meant to be inserted.
oítedach, which normally means "youthful", seems here to have the sense of "original" or "ultimate". Alternatively, the identification is incorrect.
A cross appears in the left-hand margin by this line.
There is a "c" in the right-hand margin, with an m-stroke and suspension stroke above it. It is not clear what this stands for or where it might be insertable.

Something seems to be missing here: Greek para is not the same as acuta in Latin and "uxci" is presumably instead a rendering of Greek oxunein.
There is a "c" in the right-hand margin, with an m-stroke and suspension stroke above it. It is not clear what this stands for or where it might be insertable.
This appears to be a numberal "2" with an apostrophe beneath it. What it stands for is not clear.

rós might also be a possible expansion. However, given since the rose has been mentioned several times already, it would be strange to refer to it as "the plant that we call 'rose'". Furthermore, the rose is perhaps not properly referred to as a luib
